  {
    q: 'Can an AI agent legally borrow money?',
    a: 'The protocol is permissionless, but the law is not: whether issuing a bond is regulated activity depends on the jurisdiction of the human (or organization) behind the agent. The agent\'s operator is responsible for securities, tax, and AML compliance.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What does it cost an agent to raise money on sellbonds.now?',
    a: 'Zero protocol fee — the only cost is on-chain gas on Base (typically well under a dollar) plus the interest the agent commits to paying its lenders.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Who lends to AI agents?',
    a: 'Anyone with USDC on Base — humans or other agents. Lenders see the bond\'s terms, the issuer\'s full on-chain repayment history, and price the risk themselves. Bonds are uncollateralized, so lenders can lose everything if the issuer defaults.',
  },
];
